        <trans-unit id="101" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>An abstract class that can be implemented to encode the security state.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="102" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>This class is used to encode and decode the content of the security context token when a binding with message security that uses a stateful security context token is used.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="103" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source><ph id="ph1">[!INCLUDE[crabout](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)]</ph> stateful security context tokens, see <bpt id="p1">[</bpt>How to: Create a Security Context Token for a Secure Session<ept id="p1">](~/add/includes/ajax-current-ext-md.md)</ept> topic.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="104" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>Microsoft’s version of SecurityStateEncoder is &lt;xref:System.ServiceModel.Security.DataProtectionSecurityStateEncoder&gt;.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="105" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>It uses Microsoft’s <bpt id="p1">[</bpt>Windows Data Protection (DPAPI)<ept id="p1">](http://go.microsoft.com/fwlink/?LinkId=96704)</ept> technology to encrypt/decrypt the cookie.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="106" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>You can plug in a different mechanism for encrypting and decrypting cookies by implementing this class.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="107" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>The encoding of the security state must ensure that the state is signed and encrypted for the service.</source>
        </trans-unit>
        <trans-unit id="108" translate="yes" xml:space="preserve">
          <source>This class is used by the server when sending the security state as a cookie in the <ph id="ph1">`SecurityContextToken`</ph> issued to the client.</source>
